    "comment": "Rationale: BCAN controls AMPARs and Kv channels. Using immunoprecipitation assays and high-resolution microscopy on primary culture parvalbumin (PV)-positive neurons, it is shown that the synaptic localization of GluA1-containing AMPA receptors as well as of Kv1.3 and Kv1.1 potassium channels is downregulated in the absence of Brevican.\nFig. 3 and Fig. S3 imply that BCAN is necessary for the maturation.. Experimental description: \"Hippocampi from E18 mouse embryos (both sexes) were dissected...\", Supplemental e5",
